widgets_values:
To use the picture-to-picture function, you must activate this group and load an image here. The "Extra Resolution" switch allows you to select an alternative image size to which the image will be cropped. When the switch is off, the resolution is optimized for SDXL (1.00 megapixels) and set to optimal values ‚Äã‚Äãdivisible by 64.

The "Denoise Image to Image" setting allows you to adjust the image-to-image denoising level from 0.00 to 1.00. At 0.00, the prompt has no effect; at 1.00, only the prompt is affected, and the input image is ignored. Sweet spot: 0.75

CLIP L: Keywords & Tags (SD Style). Use short, concise terms for the main subject, style, or lighting mood (e.g., "masterpiece, 8k, oil painting").

T5XXL: Natural Language. Describe the scene as you would to a human. This is where complex details, spatial relationships, and long sentences belong.

Switch: 1 - Standard Clip XXL & Clip L / 2 - Both Clip XXL / 3 - Both Clip L / 4 - Swapped. Note: Anything other than 1 usually doesn't make sense, but feel free to play around with it ‚Äì you'll quickly understand why.
